correctness.rationale: Major portions of the extraction are not traceable to the article, contain schema issues, or are internally inconsistent. Key problems include: (1) Unsupported/fabricated parameters: reactor manufacturer (Applied Materials), carrier/purging gas (Ar), reactor pressure (10 mTorr), delivery method, dosing/purge times, flow rates, optical properties (n, absorption, band gap), uniformity, conformality, roughness, film density, resistivity, carrier density, on/off ratio, threshold voltage — none are reported in the paper. (2) Schema violation: processParameters.plasmaPower is set to null, which is not an allowed type; omit this field if not using PEALD. (3) Internal inconsistencies: thicknessControl gives growthPerCycle = 0.1 Å and numberofCycles = 200 (implying ~2 nm), but filmThickness is 20 nm; deviceProperties.deviceStructure is given as “bottom-gate top-contact” while the article clearly uses BGBC (bottom-gate bottom-contact). (4) Misassignment of measurements: deviceProperties.fieldEffectMobility uses 9.9 cm^2/V·s, which is the saturation mobility (μ_sat) of Dev. A, not μ_FE as defined by the schema; materialProperties.electricalProperties.mobility is labeled “Hall measurements” with 9.9 cm^2/V·s, but the article does not report Hall mobility for IGZO films (μ_sat was extracted from TFT transfer curves). (5) Composition/process incoherence: filmComposition.atomicRatio '1:1:1.6' corresponds to composition B, while deviceProperties (μ_sat = 9.9 cm^2/V·s, SS = 240 mV/dec) correspond to Dev. A; supercycleDesign and reactantSelection do not reflect the reported sub-cycle ratios (TEIn/In–Ga/DEZn = 0:2:2, 2:2:2, 4:2:2) and bundle all precursors into one string instead of per-compound entries. (6) Partial correctness: temperature (150 °C), substrate (thermally grown SiO2/Si), oxidant (O3 for IGZO), and film thickness (20 nm) align with the article, and SS = 240 mV/dec matches Dev. A. To correct: remove or justify all unreported parameters, fix plasmaPower (omit), correct deviceStructure to BGBC, align mobility fields with the schema (use μ_FE if available or clearly state μ_sat under an allowed field), ensure composition/device data correspond to the same experiment, and represent the supercycle and precursors per compound with the reported 0:2:2 / 2:2:2 / 4:2:2 ratios.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and contains many fabricated or schema-inconsistent values. Key issues: (1) Multiple processes in the article are not represented. At minimum, distinct IGZO ALD processes for compositions A (0:2:2, 150 °C), B (2:2:2, 150 °C), C (4:2:2, 150 °C), and D (2:2:2, 200 °C) should be separate processes; gate-stack oxidant variants (H2O, O3, O2-plasma for PL; H2O vs O3 for GI) that materially affect device outcomes are also not captured. (2) Supercycle design is incorrect: it lists a single “InGaZnO” subcycle instead of the reported TEIn/In–Ga/DEZn subcycles with explicit counts (e.g., 0:2:2, 2:2:2, 4:2:2) and defined sequence. (3) Numerous parameters are untraceable to the article and appear invented: reactor manufacturer (Applied Materials), carrier/purge gas (Ar), chamber pressure (10 mTorr), dosing/purge times, flow rates, GPC (0.1 Å/cycle), uniformity, conformality, roughness, density, optical properties, and film electrical properties (“Hall measurements”), none of which are reported. (4) Internal inconsistency: 200 cycles at 0.1 Å/cycle would yield ~2 nm, not the reported 20 nm film; yet film thickness is set to 20 nm. (5) Device-level fields are inaccurate: device structure is given as bottom-gate top-contact, but the article uses bottom-gate bottom-contact; threshold voltage and on/off ratio are not reported; “fieldEffectMobility” uses a value (9.9 cm2/V·s) corresponding to μ_sat of Dev. A, not μ_FE. (6) Schema issues: plasmaPower is set to null (type mismatch; should be omitted or provided with QUDT-compliant power units if PEALD is used); reactantSelection lumps “TEIn/In-Ga/DEZn” into one precursor string rather than per-compound entries; supercycleDesign lacks required, article-backed content. To improve completeness, add separate processes for A–D with correct temperatures and supercycle counts/sequence, correct device structure, include only article-supported values (e.g., XPS-derived compositions and In/Ga/Zn ratios), and remove invented parameters (pressure, flows, dosing times, optical/roughness/density, etc.) unless verifiably reported.
